----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox
##JVCL:Component
<TITLEIMG TJvColorComboBox>
<GROUP JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos, JVCL.SelectAndChoose>
Summary
  Combo box that enables the user to select a color from a drop-down list.
Description
  TJvColorComboBox is a TJvCustomComboBox descendant which enables the user to select a
  color from a drop-down list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorDialogText
Summary
  Specifies the display text for the special combo box item, used to select a color from a dialog.
Description
  Use ColorDialogText to specify a new string for the combo box item, used to select a color from
  a dialog. Thus, if the user selects this item, the component displays a dialog for selecting colors.
  
  If the user selects a color from the dialog, a new item is added to the combobox, with text specified
  by NewColorText, and color as selected in the dialog.
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't display this special
  item.
See Also
  NewColorText, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorValue
Summary
  Specifies the color value that is displayed in the edit box.
Description
  Use the ColorValue property to read the color value of the current selected color or specify a new
  color for the ColorValue value, to change the current selected color.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.ColorWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width, in pixels, of the color boxes.
Description
  Use ColorWidth to specify the width of the color boxes.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.DroppedDownWidth
Summary
  Specifies the width, in pixels, of the drop-down list. 
Description
  Use DropDownWidth to customize the width of the drop-down list.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.HiliteColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteColor to read or change the background color of the text that is focused. The focused line
  is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
See Also
  HiliteText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.HiliteText
Summary
  Specifies the color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteText to specify the color of the text characters (as opposed to the background color) of
  the focused line. The focused text is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
  
  If Color is set to a dithered color, the text appears in the closest non-dithered value.
See Also
  HiliteColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.NewColorText
Summary
  Specifies the prefix for the display text of new colors added by the user.
Description
  Use NewColorText to specify a prefix for the text of colors added by the user. The user can add
  colors to the combo box by selecting the special combo box item - with text ColorDialogText. 
  
  If the user selects a color from the dialog, a new item is added to the combobox. The display text
  of this item consist of the NewColorText and a number indicating the number of custom colors added
  by the user, so far. 
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't allow colors to be added
  by the user.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, OnNewColor, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.OnNewColor
Summary
  Occurs when the users adds a new color to the combo box.
Description
  \Write an OnNewColor event handler to take specific actions as an user adds a new color to the
  combo box.
Parameters
  Sender      - The TJvColorComboBox component that has sent this event.
  Color       - The new color added by the user.
  DisplayName - The display text for the new color. It consists of the NewColorText and a number
                indicating the number of custom colors added by the user, so far. Alter DisplayName
                to change the display text for the new color.
  AllowAdd    - Set AllowAdd to True to allow the new color to be added to the combo box. Set AllowAdd
                To False to disallow the new color to be added.
Note
  coCustomColors must be included in Options, otherwise the combobox doesn't allow colors to be added
  by the user.
See Also
  ColorDialogText, NewColorText, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboBox.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of the color combo box.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the appearance and functionality of the combo box.
  
  Use Options to
  
  * Specify how the color value must be displayed.
  * Enable the user to add colors to the combo box.
  * Add the system colors to the combo box.
See Also
  TJvColorComboOption
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboOption
Summary
  Defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a color combo box.
Description
  The TJvColorComboOption type defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a color
  combo box.

  TJvColorComboOptions is a set of TJvColorComboOption values.

  The following table lists the possible values:
@@TJvColorComboOption.coText
  Displays the name of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coHex
  Displays the hexadecimal value of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coRGB
  Displays the RGB value of the color.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coSysColors
  Adds the system colors such as clWindow to the combo box.
@@TJvColorComboOption.coCustomColors
  Allows the user to add colors to the combo box, by selecting the special combo box item with text
  ColorDialogText.
See Also
  TJvColorComboBox.Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvColorComboOptions
<COMBINEWITH TJvColorComboOption>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox
##JVCL:Component
<TITLEIMG TJvFontComboBox>
<GROUP JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Combos, JVCL.SelectAndChoose>
Summary
  Combo box that enables the user to select a font from a drop-down list.
Description
  TJvFontCombobox is a TJvCustomComboBox descendant which enables the user to select a
  font from a drop-down list of the face names for all fonts supported by the
  screen /installed on the system.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.Device
Summary
  Specifies the device from which to retrieve the list of available fonts.
Description
  These are the possible values of Device:
  <TABLE>
  Value         Meaning
  -----         -------
  fdScreen      Retrieve from the screen.
  fdPrinter     Retrieve from the printer.
  fdBoth        Retrieve from both the screen and the printer.
  </TABLE>
See Also
  UseImages
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.FontName
Summary
  Specifies the font name that is displayed in the edit box.
Description
  Use the FontName property to read the text of the combo box or specify a new string for the FontName 
  value, to change the current selected font name.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.HiliteColor
Summary
  Specifies the background color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteColor to read or change the background color of the text that is focused. The focused line
  is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
See Also
  HiliteText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.HiliteText
Summary
  Specifies the color of the text that is focused.
Description
  Use HiliteText to specify the color of the text characters (as opposed to the background color) of
  the focused line. The focused text is painted using highlight colors, to make it stand out.
  
  If Color is set to a dithered color, the text appears in the closest non-dithered value.
See Also
  HiliteColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of the font combo box.
Description
  Use the Options property to customize the appearance and functionality of the combo box.
  
  Use Options to
  
  * Specify which type of fonts the combobox should contain.
  * Display each font name in the combo box using the specific font.
See Also
  TJvFontComboOptions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboBox.UseImages
Summary
  Specifies whether to use images to indicate the font type.
Description
  If UseImages is set to True, the combobox uses images to indicate the font type. Set UseImages to
  False, to disable showing images.
  
  The following table lists the possible images and their meaning.  
  <TABLE>
  Image                       Font Type
  -----                       ---------
  <IMAGE FontType_TrueType>   TrueType font.
  <IMAGE FontType_Printer>    The printer supports downloading this TrueType font.
  <IMAGE FontType_Fixed>      Other font, such as vector or raster fonts.
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOption
Summary
  Defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a font combo box.
Description
  The TJvFontComboOption type defines values that control the appearance and behavior of a font
  combo box.

  TJvFontComboOptions is a set of TJvFontComboOption values.

  The following table lists the possible values:
@@TJvFontComboOption.foAnsiOnly
  Displays only fonts that use the Windows character set. Symbol fonts are not listed in the dialog.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foTrueTypeOnly
  Displays only TrueType fonts in the dialog. Other fonts are not listed.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foFixedPitchOnly
  Displays only monospaced fonts in the dialog. Proportionally spaced fonts are not listed, nor are
  TrueType fonts that do not have the fixed-pitch flag set in the style header.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foNoOEMFonts
  Removes OEM fonts from the combo box. Lists only non-OEM fonts.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foOEMFontsOnly
  Displays only OEM fonts in the combo box.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foScalableOnly
  Displays only scalable fonts in the combo box. Non-scalable (bitmap) fonts are removed from the list.
@@TJvFontComboOption.foWysiWyg
  Displays each font name in the combo box using the specific font.
See Also
  TJvFontComboBox.Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFontComboOptions
<COMBINEWITH TJvFontComboOption>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
